  "prompt": "What aspect of studying at Oxford has surprised you the most?",
  "response": "While I don't have personal experiences, I can share that many students often express surprise about the close-knit community at Oxford. Despite its reputation as a prestigious institution, many find that the tutorial system fosters intimate learning environments where they receive personalized attention from tutors. This direct engagement can lead to deep intellectual discussions, which is different from the larger lecture formats at other universities. Additionally, the rich history and traditions, such as formal hall dining and various ceremonies, also tend to astonish newcomers. Overall, the blend of academic rigor and community atmosphere is a common theme among those who study there.",
